{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b48df5a4-c637-4bd4-955c-ac68ec1595f1","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFix: reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_gyfonRKEs53DpXBs1H9i9o","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2b8b349a8e1a439492ef582bb0fcbab6/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2b8b349a8e1a439492ef582bb0fcbab6/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"94152181-2cd4-4b24-851c-c92f1922ad88","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — depends on `Domain.fs` via `open BrokenOrder.Domain`\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) — depends on both\n\nThe problem is that `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`. In F#, files must be ordered so that dependencies come first.\n\n\nThe solution is to reorder the files in the project so `Domain.fs` comes first, followed by `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":494,"requestId":"73CB:8E236:15A1741:182FB7C:6A051E2F"},"id":"e58e514e-4bc8-46e1-bdd2-db1b889488ba","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:58:32.942Z","parentId":"46323a9e-bb3a-4d1d-8214-2745d9bcff56"}
